author: Telegraph Staff
title: Which beers will a combined ABInBev-SABMiller own? In pictures
text:
A merger of two of the world's biggest brewers is on the cards. But which world-famous beer brands will it bring together? 
Stella Artois: One of the UK’s best-selling beers, AB’s Stella is sold in over 100 countries and recently spawned a cider - or Cidre - spin-off. Its name comes from the latin for “star”, Stella, and Artois, for Sebastian Artois, the owner of the original Belgian brewery where it was made. Picture: Qilai Shen
